Task
Build a complete full-stack web application called Student Service Portal. The application must allow students to view information, submit data, and see dynamic updates from the backend.

Frontend Requirements

Use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks required)
The UI must be clean UI and visually appealing
The design must follow mobile responsive design principles
Create exactly 6 different pages
Home Page (Welcome + overview + navigation)
Registration Page (student registration form)
Service Request Page (submit requests or issues)
Dashboard Page (view submitted data dynamically)
Announcements Page (display updatesevents)
ContactAbout Page
Include navigation bar on all pages
Use JavaScript to fetch and display backend data dynamically

Backend Requirements

Use Node.js with Express.js
Backend must handle API requests
Implement REST API endpoints
GET → fetch data from database
POST → add new data
Use middleware like body-parser or built-in JSON parsing
Enable CORS for frontend-backend communication

Database Requirement

Use JSON file as database
Store all student registrations and service requests in the JSON file
Read and write data using Node.js file system (fs module)

Dynamic Functionality

Form submissions should send data to backend using POST API
Dashboard page should display real-time data using GET API
Updates should reflect without manually editing files

Project Structure

Organize code into folders
frontend → HTML, CSS, JS
backend → server.js, routes, JSON database
Maintain clean and readable code structure

Additional Requirements

Use proper comments in code
Ensure all pages are connected via navigation
Handle basic errors (e.g., empty form submission)
Make the UI user-friendly and professional

Output Expected

Complete frontend code for all 6 pages
Backend server code
JSON database file
Working API endpoints (GET and POST)
Fully functional application that can run locally

Important Instructions (Must Follow)

Use clean UI
Mobile responsive design
Use JSON file as database
Backend must handle API requests